text: The Cathedral of Almería (), in full the Cathedral of the Incarnation of Almería (), is a Roman Catholic cathedral in Almería, Andalusia. It is the seat of the Diocese of Almería. The cathedral was built in Gothic and Renaissance architectural styles from 1524 to 1562. Its last bell was built in 1805. ==References== Category:Roman Catholic cathedrals in Spain Category:Almería Category:16th-century buildings and structures Category:1560s establishments
